it's not necessary to wrap it into another try/except block. you can write:

```py
try:
    ...
except (ProgrammingError, LocationParseError) as e:
   ...
except Exception as e:
   ...
```

This is causing the missing symbols with clang/C++14. The `descr` part must be made explicitly `constexpr` to avoid needing a definition for `digits` (i.e. `PYBIND11_DESCR` in place of `constexpr auto` for compatiblity with C++11). The following lines along with removing the `digits` definition reduces binary size slightly for me:

```c++
PYBIND11_DESCR name = _("(") + detail::array_info<T>::extents() + _(")");
return name.text() + format_descriptor<detail::remove_all_extents_t<T>>::format();
```

This check could be more precise. The only providers that we expect to be missing parent information are the default providers for a stack; any explicitly instantiated providers should have accurate parent information. We're leaning on the fact that this test does not explicitly instantiate any providers in order to keep the check a bit more concise.

Regarding parenting default providers: I do not believe that we should add parent information for these resources. I suspect that we may want to allow explicitly-instantiated default providers in the future by allowing a program to do something like the following:

```
pulumi.runWithDefaultProviders(..., {
    aws: new aws.Provider(...),
    gcp: new gcp.Provider(...),
    // ...etc
});
```

Where `runWithDefaultProviders` will instantiate a stack resource with the given provider map and things will just work out using the parent information.
